OL,4,CFirms 'lose trillions' by ignoring
OL,5,Cdisabled consumers
OL,6, Some of the world's biggest firms have
OL,7, signed up to a campaign which aims to
OL,8, tackle prejudice towards disabled
OL,9, people in the business world.
OL,11,FCompanies with combined sales of more
OL,12,Fthan $8 trillion and 20 million staff,
OL,13,Fincluding Apple, BP and Coca-Cola have
OL,14,Fjoined the Valuable 500 initiative.
OL,16,FBut founder Caroline Casey said the
OL,17,Fcampaign was not just about employing
OL,18,Fmore people with disabilities.
OL,20,FFirms are losing $13tn in sales by
OL,21,Fignoring disabled consumers, she said.
